result.execSummary:
The defendant Jamie L Myren was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes:
The $10,000 Fine is STAYED as long as the defendant maintains No Contact with L.S. and stays out of La Crosse

The Court will remove $500 from the Fine of $10,000 for every 90 days there is no contact with L.S. and the defendant does not return to the City of La Crosse

The DA's office is to inform the Clerk of Court office every 90 days if the defendant has complied with this No Contact with L.S. and City of La Crosse
.

The defendant is to pay Court costs/fees totalling $518.  Payment plan is $50 per month with the first payment due in 90 days (5-23-2022) and each subsequent payment will be due the 23rd of each month thereafter until paid in full.  Fail to pay will result in a Judgment being entered and collected through WI Debt Collection
.
